algorithms.imageProcessing

Class FixedSizeSortedVector<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • algorithms.imageProcessing.FixedSizeSortedVector<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - class type to be held and sorted by this class. It must implement Comparable.

    public class FixedSizeSortedVector<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
    a class to hold a fixed number of items of type T which are kept in a sorted stated. 
     runtime complexity is:
     O(N * (lg_2(k) + smaller than k))
 where k is the fixed capacity and N is the number of times add is used.
 
 worse case runtime complexity is O(N * (k + lg_2(k)))
 best case runtime complexity is O(N * (1 + lg_2(k)))
    Author:
    nichole

      • add

        public boolean add(T value)
        add value to the fixed size sorted list using (T).compareTo to order the items in the internal list. runtime complexity is O(log_2(capacity) + less than capacity).
        Parameters:
        value -
        Returns:
        true if added, else false

      • getArray

        public T[] getArray()
        get the internal array for the sorted list. note this is not a copy in order to keep the use small, so do not edit it and continue to use the add method. runtime complexity is O(1)
        Returns:

      • getNumberOfItems

        public int getNumberOfItems()
        return the number of items in the internal array. if the array is not yet filled, the return will be less than the capacity, else will be the same as the capacity.
        Returns:
